# Display API (DAT 0.7)

Guide for the Display capability bridge in **expo-meta-wearables-dat**.

## Overview

Display renders declarative UI on **Meta Ray-Ban Display** glasses. This package exposes it to React Native via a JSON content tree that native code converts to the SDK DSL.

```
JS DisplayContentNode â†’ DisplayContentBuilder â†’ mwdat-display / MWDATDisplay â†’ lenses
Captouch tap â†’ onDisplayInteraction { interactionId }
```

## Prerequisites

| Requirement | Version |
|-------------|---------|
| DAT SDK | 0.7.0 |
| Meta AI app | V272+ |
| Display firmware | V125+ |
| Hardware | Meta Ray-Ban Display |
| DAM | `damEnabled: true` in config plugin |

MockDeviceKit **does not** simulate display rendering.

## Config plugin (DAM)

```json
["expo-meta-wearables-dat", {
  "urlScheme": "myapp",
  "damEnabled": true
}]
```

- Android: `<meta-data android:name="com.meta.wearable.mwdat.DAM_ENABLED" android:value="true" />`
- iOS: `MWDAT.DAMEnabled = true` in Info.plist

Camera-only apps leave `damEnabled` unset (default `false`).

## TypeScript API

```typescript
await addDisplayToSession(sessionId);
await sendDisplayContent(sessionId, contentTree);
await removeDisplayFromSession(sessionId);

addListener("onDisplayStateChange", ({ sessionId, state }) => { /* stopped|starting|started|stopping */ });
addListener("onDisplayInteraction", ({ sessionId, interactionId }) => { /* onPressId from tree */ });
addListener("onDisplayError", ({ sessionId, error }) => { /* capabilityDenied, invalidSessionState, ... */ });
```

Root node of `contentTree` must be `type: "flexBox"`.

## DisplayContentNode (MVP)

Defined in `src/EMWDAT.types.ts`:

| type | key fields |
|------|------------|
| `flexBox` | `direction?`, `gap?`, `paddingAll?`, `onPressId?`, `children[]` |
| `text` | `content`, `style?` (heading/body/meta), `color?` |
| `button` | `label`, `style?`, `onPressId` (required) |
| `image` | `uri`, `sizePreset?` (icon/fill) |
| `icon` | `name`, `style?` (filled/outline) |

Tap handling: set `onPressId` on `flexBox` or `button`; native emits `onDisplayInteraction` â€” **no JS callbacks in native code**.

## Native implementation

### Android

- `DisplaySessionManager.kt` â€” `session.addDisplay()`, state flow, `display.sendContent { }`
- `DisplayContentBuilder.kt` â€” recursive `ContentScope` builder from `Map<String, Any>`

### iOS

- `DisplaySessionManager.swift` â€” `session.addDisplay()`, `await display.start()`, `display.send(rootView)`
- `DisplayContentBuilder.swift` â€” builds `FlexBox`, `Text`, `Button`, etc. from `[String: Any]`

Both wired in `EMWDATModule` with events `onDisplayStateChange`, `onDisplayInteraction`, `onDisplayError`.

## Usage flow

1. `configure()` â†’ register â†’ `createSession()` â†’ `startSession()`
2. `addDisplayToSession(sessionId)`
3. Wait for `onDisplayStateChange` â†’ `state === "started"`
4. `sendDisplayContent(sessionId, tree)`
5. Handle `onDisplayInteraction` for taps
6. `removeDisplayFromSession(sessionId)` or `stopSession(sessionId)`

## Adding a new node type

1. Extend `DisplayContentNode` union in `src/EMWDAT.types.ts`
2. Add builder branch in `DisplayContentBuilder.kt` and `DisplayContentBuilder.swift`
3. Add type test in `src/__tests__/types.test.ts`
4. Document in README Display section

## Out of scope (do not implement without explicit request)

- Video playback on display
- Full icon catalog mapping
- MockDeviceKit display simulation
- Thermal monitoring bridge

